%20separate%20order%20on%20Uber%20Eats%20using%20Georgia's%20phone.%20The%20court%20upheld%20the%20company's%20argument%20that%20by%20agreeing%20to%20Uber's%20terms%20during%20that%20transaction%2C%20the%20family%20waived%20their%20right%20to%20pursue%20claims%20in%20court.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20couple%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20their%20minor%20daughter%2C%20using%20Georgia's%20phone%2C%20who%20accepted%20the%20terms%20of%20service%20for%20Uber%20Eats%20by%20clicking%20a%20button%20that%20falsely%20confirmed%20she%20was%20over%2018.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20concluded%20the%20arbitration%20agreement%2C%20which%20covers%20auto%20accidents%20and%20personal%20injuries%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Cvalid%20and%20enforceable.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20response%2C%20Uber%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F10%2F02%2Fbusiness%2Fuber-eats-accident-lawsuit%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Georgia%20%E2%80%9Cagreed%20to%20Uber's%20terms%20of%20use%2C%20including%20the%20arbitration%20agreement%2C%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20even%20took%20rides%20after%20agreeing.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20plaintiffs%20continue%20to%20tell%20the%20press%20that%20it%20was%20their%20daughter%20who%20ordered%20Uber%20Eats%20and%20accepted%20the%20terms%20of%20use%2C%20it's%20worth%20noting%20that%20in%20court%20they%20could%20only%20%E2%80%98surmise'%20that%20that%20was%20the%20case%20but%20could%20not%20recall%20whether%20%E2%80%98their%20daughter%20ordered%20food%20independently%20or%20if%20Georgia%20assisted%2C%26quot%3B%20CNN%20quoted%20a%20spokesperson%20as%20saying.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20couple%20expressed%20disappointment%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20%E2%80%9Csurprised%20and%20heartbroken%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20ruling.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20horrified%20at%20what%20the%20court's%20decision%20suggests%3A%20A%20large%20corporation%20l